  "content_markdown": "Version: 8.0All Creatio products\nOn this page\nMini pages allow users to work with the essential data of a record without opening the record page. Use Creatio mini pages to **add** (Fig. 1), **edit** (Fig. 2), and **view** record data. The set of fields is different for each type of mini page and is configured separately. Mini pages and mini-page layout are configured in the [Section wizard](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1906). You can add a mini-page to any Creatio section.\nFig. 1Adding a new record via mini page\n![Fig. 1Adding a new record via mini page](https://academy.creatio.com/guides/sites/en/files/documentation/user/en/base/BPMonlineHelp/chapter_minicards/chapter_minicards_add_a_record.png)\nHover the mouse pointer over a record hyperlink to display a mini page. Mini pages only contain fields filled in the record page.\nFig. 2Account mini page\n![Fig. 2Account mini page](https://academy.creatio.com/guides/sites/en/files/documentation/user/en/base/BPMonlineHelp/chapter_minicards/chapter_minicards_company.png)\nWith mini pages, you can perform the basic actions available on the edit pages of the corresponding records, such as view the phone number, send an email or go to the connected records. If a specific field is not available on the mini page or if you need to populate the details, click ![chapter_minicards_expand.png](https://academy.creatio.com/guides/sites/en/files/documentation/user/en/base/BPMonlineHelp/chapter_minicards/chapter_minicards_expand.png) in the top right corner of the mini page to open the main record page.\nThe user can click ![chapter_minicards_edit.png](https://academy.creatio.com/guides/sites/default/files/documentation/user/ru/ui_business_logic_customization/BPMonlineHelp/add_mini_pages/chapter_minicards_edit.png) in the top right corner of the mini page to edit the record.\nYou can exit the edit mode by clicking the ![btn_basis_filters_close_search_panel.png](https://academy.creatio.com/guides/sites/en/files/documentation/user/en/base/BPMonlineHelp/chapter_minicards/btn_basis_filters_close_search_panel.png) button or pressing the \"Esc\" key.\n* * *\n## See also\u200b\n[How to configure mini pages for using in a section](https://academy.bpmonline.com/documents?product=administration&ver=7&id=1949&document=studio)\n[Mini page](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=15591)",
